# Project Structure Guide

This project is an Astro site with TailwindCSS and DaisyUI, deployed via Netlify.

- Core config lives in [astro.config.mjs](mdc:astro.config.mjs) and [tailwind.config.cjs](mdc:tailwind.config.cjs)
- Global site settings live in [src/config.ts](mdc:src/config.ts)
- Content collections are defined in [src/content/config.ts](mdc:src/content/config.ts)
- Pages are in [src/pages](mdc:src/pages) with blog routes at:
  - [src/pages/blog/[...page].astro](mdc:src/pages/blog/[...page].astro) for the paginated list
  - [src/pages/blog/[slug].astro](mdc:src/pages/blog/[slug].astro) for individual posts
- Layouts live in [src/layouts](mdc:src/layouts):
  - [src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro](mdc:src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro)
  - [src/layouts/PostLayout.astro](mdc:src/layouts/PostLayout.astro)
  - [src/layouts/StoreItemLayout.astro](mdc:src/layouts/StoreItemLayout.astro)
- Components are in [src/components](mdc:src/components) including sidebar, header, and cards
- RSS feed is generated by [src/pages/rss.xml.js](mdc:src/pages/rss.xml.js)
- Slug utility is [src/lib/createSlug.ts](mdc:src/lib/createSlug.ts)

Conventions:
- Use `createSlug(title, slug)` when linking to blog posts so links match static paths
- Prefer layout components over duplicating structure in pages
- Keep MD content frontmatter consistent with schemas in `src/content/config.ts`
